Paper

Target IP: 10.129.136.31

Scanning


There are three TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH, HTTP, and HTTPS.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

Browsing to this port displays the webpage above.


Intercepting the GET request shows there is a domain name for office.paper. After appending this name to the /etc/hosts and visiting the domain name shows the webpage above. The target host is using WordPress 5.2.3.


Doing a Google search for this application version shows it is vulnerable, as shown above.

Exploitation


Using the payload ?static=1 displays the secret webpage above. Apparently there is a secret registration URL. Since this is another vhost, I will append this to the /etc/hosts file.


Browsing to the secret URL displays the webpage above. After registering for a new account, I checked the general chat.


Apparently the credentials are stored in /hubot/.env directory. Meaning we can access this file using file ../hubot/.env.
Now I have the credentials for the hubot recyclops:Queenofblad3s!23.


There is one user called dwight. Maybe I can spray the password for the user dwight? And it worked! Now I am logged in as dwight.

Privilege Escalation

Running sudo -V shows it is 1.8.29, which has CVE-2021-3650. This host is vulnerable to the exploit according to LinPeas output.

Running this privilege escalation exploit gives me a root shell.

Flags


The user.txt flag once I gained a foothold on the machine by spraying the password from hubot config file against the user dwight.


The root.txt flag once I used the exploit to gain a root shell.
